  "comments": "This coin was minted again in 1789 with unknown purpose but this restrike are recognizable by the wider King&#039;s neck and the presence of a &quot;1764&quot; embossement on the coin edge. These ancient restrikes are minted in Altona<br /><br />\r\nThe necklace of the Order of the Elephant has twelve tower and twelve elephant elements plus the pendant. Laurel sprigs are thin and with few leaves and berries.<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/624171fe663c4.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/624171fe663c4.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"98\" /></a>",
